## Module 5 Topic 5 Migrations, archiving and monitoring

BCM - Business Continuity Management

DR - Disaster Recovery  
policies outline the procedures and processes that an organisation follows to restore operations after a disruptive event, such as natural disasters, cyber-attacks, or system failures.

IR - Incident Response 
is a critical component of DR, focusing on the immediate actions taken to mitigate the impact of incidents.

BIA - Business Impact Analysis 
Evaluate the potential consequences of disruptions on critical business functions.

Recovery Objectives:
Recovery Time Objective (RTO): The maximum acceptable length of time that a system can be down.
Recovery Point Objective (RPO): The maximum acceptable amount of data loss measured in time.
